== CC-BY compatibility  ==

I know I just got done accepting that maybe CC-BY might be compatible with GFDL after all. Today someone else wondering about CC-BY compatible pointed out [[w:Wikipedia talk:FAQ/Copyright#CC-BY compatability issue, remove from FAQ?]] which suggests that even the Wikimedia Foundation's own legal counsel doesn't believe CC-BY and GFDL are compatible. http://www.fsf.org/licensing/licenses/index_html#OtherLicenses says the same thing. Perhaps as was said on the FAQ talk page, it is unwise after all to jump to conclusions either way if even the experts can't agree. --<span style="font: bold 10pt 'courier new', comic, sans, ms;">[[User:Darklama|<font color="midnightblue">dark</font>]][[User_talk:Darklama|<font color="green">lama</font>]]</span> 20:17, 26 May 2009 (UTC)

== [[Chemical synthesis]] == {| cellspacing="5" cellpadding="5" style="border: 1px red solid; background: #ffffcc; width: 95%; margin: auto; color: #000000;" | style="width: 40px; text-align: center;" | [[Image:Stop hand.svg|30px]] | Closed as '''delete''' '''&ndash; [[User:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">Mike.lifeguard</font>]]''' &#124; <sup>[[User talk:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">talk</font>]]</sup> 00:02, 25 October 2007 (UTC) |- | colspan="2" style="border-top: 1px red dashed;" |
:{{Vd}} - This book has been here before and while at VfD I remembered the controversy it caused and now feel it should be re-assessed. The amount of red warnings on this book are immense and have grown over time. I think it's dangerous to house this book here since I don't think it takes safety concerns seriously enough and I don't believe there's any academic value in its content. -[[User:Withinfocus|<font color="#000000">'''within'''</font>]][[User talk:Withinfocus|<font color="#7A7A7A">'''focus'''</font>]] 15:54, 12 October 2007 (UTC) :{{Vote/Merge}} - to a chem lab manual (not sure what's available, but there ought to be something) but {{Vd}} the stupid stuff like nitro and TNT. If it can't be done in class, it shouldn't be on Wikibooks. Also, a single standardized risk disclaimer template at the top of each page should be sufficient - there's no need for the mess of warnings this book uses. '''&ndash; [[User:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">Mike.lifeguard</font>]]''' &#124; <sup>[[User talk:Mike.lifeguard|<font color="Indigo">talk</font>]]</sup> 16:11, 12 October 2007 (UTC) :{{Vd}} The old VfD (very lengthy) is located [http://en.wikibooks.org/wiki/Wikibooks:Votes_for_deletion/Archive_13#Chemical_synthesis.2FAcetone_peroxide HERE]. I would like to summarize some of my opinions, and some opinions that other people articulated from that previous discussion: :#This book is, essentially, a "How to make explosives at home, using chemicals you can purchase at a store" guide. As such, it is non-academic (because instructions of these types are never taught in a respectable school) and it is dangerous. The only recipe that I can find that is not an explosive is the Asprin recipe, and since that's a medicine intended to be taken internally, it too has potential for danger. :#People attempting to follow these instructions are putting themselves in serious danger due to the explosive nature of these recipes. Without being able to safely reproduce the results, and since these instructions are not academic, it is not possible to verify this information. This is a violation of the [[WB:NOR]] policy, where material must be reproducible "safely and reliably". :#This book is just a listing of various recipes without any discussion, or central narrative. As such, it violates the macropedia clause of the [[WB:WIW]] policy. :#The previous VfD was ended under the assumption that the book would be improved in a number of ways. This includes, but was not limited to: Fixing the recipes so they are not as informal or dangerous, adding non-explosive recipes (the only addition has been Asprin, which is still dangerous) to make the book more comprehensive, and updating the book so it was no longer a macropedia. None of these conditions have been met since the previous VfD, leading me to believe that they never will be met. :I apologize if I am being overly verbose, but I am strongly in favor of deleting this book, and am attempting to summarize a very lengthy VfD discussion. --'''Whiteknight'''&nbsp;([[User:Whiteknight|Page]])&nbsp;([[User talk:Whiteknight|Talk]]) 16:27, 12 October 2007 (UTC) :{{Vd}} I can't see the purpose of this book. I'm not against hosting things that might be illegal in one country but legal in others but this book seems to have no value and is poorly written. [[User:Xania|Xania]] [[Image:Flag_of_Italy.svg|15px]][[User talk:Xania|<sup>talk</sup>]] 19:13, 14 October 2007 (UTC) :{{Vd}} While I think we could have a chemical synthesis book, this surely isn't it, especially since this is supposed to be meant for an academic setting. I don't agree that it's a macropedia, there are textbooks on chemical synthesis that are not necessarily tied together by a central theme, but are nonetheless very useful when coupled to a text on, say, organic chemistry. :however, the point about it being unverifiable is well taken. [[User:Mattb112885|Mattb112885]] <small> ([[User talk:Mattb112885|talk to me]]) </small> 02:08, 18 October 2007 (UTC