Stamp collecting came first and eventually evolved into the study of the technical and historical side of things, collectively called: philately. 

The word "<font color="red">phila</font>" comes from the Greek, meaning "love"; while "<font color="red">ateli</font>" means "postage dues". {citation needed} Philately, therefore, is basically the study of postage items: stamps, first-day-covers, miniature sheets, etc including the manner on how they are created, what materials are used. {citation needed}

[[Category:{{FULLBOOKNAME}}|{{FULLCHAPTERNAME}}]]

==Introduction==

Although stamp collecting is the most popular hobby, the natural progression of a stamp collector is to become a philatelist, ultimately. One doesn't just stop collecting stamps, mount them in philatelic albums, then just let them gather dust.

