== Footnotes ==
#{{note|mro}} Perl 5.95 adds a new pragma ''mro'' which uses C3 resolution. This pragma is however opt in and makes a few tools available to you, which can all be utilized maintaining reverse compatibility with older perls using MRO::Compat.
#{{note|dfs}} The method that made little sense is called Depth First Search (DFS). DFS was the predecessor MRO to C3 in perl. Briefly, it did not handle any form of triangle inheritance in a sane fashion.

